The paper deals with the problem of transforming a given graph into a desired graph using a set of local graph transformation primitives. This problem is related to graph algorithms and graph theory, which are covered by the computer science sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these sub-categories, cs.DS and cs.SI are the most likely as they directly deal with graph algorithms and networks, while cs.DM, cs.CG, and cs.LG are also relevant due to their focus on discrete mathematics, computational geometry, and machine learning, respectively.
